# Patch 0028 — Kavacha Component Marketplace (about:marketplace)
# (ROADMAP Phase 3; ADR 0010).
#
# WHAT: an offline-first component marketplace. KavachaMarketplace.sys.mjs is a
# process singleton that ships a BUNDLED, trusted catalog of components — themes
# (referencing KavachaThemeEngine built-ins), layout presets (partial layout
# docs), and bundles (ordered steps, e.g. "Research Mode" = Forest theme + a
# reading layout) — installs them into the profile
# (kavacha-marketplace/installed.json), and APPLIES them by delegating to the
# engines that already ship: KavachaThemeEngine.setActiveTheme (patch 0023) and
# KavachaLayoutEngine.setLayout (patch 0022). It has no application path of its
# own. about:marketplace is a privileged chrome page (a JS nsIAboutModule, same
# pattern as about:studio / ADR 0009) that renders the catalog grouped by type
# and drives the engine through its public API.
#
# WHY: this supersedes the theme-only marketplace named in earlier ADRs with a
# single surface for every customization component. It is offline-first because
# accounts/network are Phase 5 — so it sideloads a first-party catalog and
# installs locally; remote install, ratings, and auto-update are deferred.
#
# DOGFOODS PATCH 0027: each installed component registers an "Apply: <name>"
# palette command through the completed registry, attributed to
# source="marketplace:<id>" so uninstall revokes it as a group
# (unregisterBySource). Runtime commands carry a literal rawLabel (they cannot
# add .ftl keys) with l10nId as identity only — exactly the 0027 contract. The
# single "Open Marketplace" entry command is likewise a runtime registration
# (source "kavacha-marketplace"), so no registry/.ftl edit is needed (that stays
# patch 0029's concern).
#
# RESERVED, HOSTLESS TYPES: the KavachaComponentType enum reserves "widget" and
# "panel" for Phase 3's sidebar-widget / tool-panel hosts, which do not exist
# yet. No installer ships for them and the bundled catalog carries none — an
# install() of such a type throws until a host engine lands (ADR 0010).
#
# NOT BUILD-VERIFIED: authored against the post-0027 tree; run
# `git -C browser/zen-upstream apply --check` + a Marionette pass (open
# about:marketplace, install/apply/remove a theme, layout, and the Research Mode
# bundle; confirm the palette gains/loses "Apply: ..." commands) before marking
# the ROADMAP item verified. Adds src/zen/common/sys/KavachaMarketplace.sys.mjs
# and src/zen/kavacha-marketplace/* (KavachaAboutMarketplace.sys.mjs,
# components.conf, jar.inc.mn, moz.build, marketplace.html/css/js); touches
# src/zen/common/modules/ZenStartup.mjs, src/zen/common/moz.build,
# src/zen/moz.build, src/browser/base/content/zen-assets.jar.inc.mn. Applies on
# top of 0027.
